{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PvSbTZEFbJFUC8m8QVesV3","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: PRD-560.2\n3\ttitle: Update commit_transcript.py for .jsonl extension\n4\tkind: task\n5\tstatus: ready\n6\tpriority: medium\n7\teffort: xs\n8\tcapability: simple\n9\tparent: \"[[PRD-560-transcripts-should-be-jsonl-files]]\"\n10\tdepends_on:\n11\t  - \"[[PRD-560.1-rewrite-transcript-assembly-jsonl]]\"\n12\tblocks: []\n13\timpacts:\n14\t  - src/darkfactory/builtins/commit_transcript.py\n15\tworkflow:\n16\ttarget_version:\n17\tcreated: 2026-04-09\n18\tupdated: 2026-04-09\n19\ttags: []\n20\t---\n21\t\n22\t# Update commit_transcript.py for .jsonl extension\n23\t\n24\t## Summary\n25\t\n26\tUpdate `commit_transcript.py` to look for `.jsonl` transcript files instead of `.log` files when copying from the transient location to the committed location. Change both the source glob/path and the destination filename to use the `.jsonl` extension.\n27\t\n28\t## Requirements\n29\t\n30\t1. Change the transient transcript source path from `.harness-transcripts/{prd_id}.log` to `.harness-transcripts/{prd_id}.jsonl`.\n31\t2. Change the committed transcript destination path from `.darkfactory/transcripts/{prd_id}-{timestamp}.log` to `.darkfactory/transcripts/{prd_id}-{timestamp}.jsonl`.\n32\t3. Ensure any glob patterns or file-existence checks in the commit logic reference `.jsonl`.\n33\t\n34\t## Technical Approach\n35\t\n36\t### File: `src/darkfactory/builtins/commit_transcript.py` (~lines 36-58)\n37\t\n38\tFind all references to `.log` in this file and replace with `.jsonl`. This includes:\n39\t\n40\t- The source path construction for finding the transient transcript.\n41\t- The destination path construction for the committed transcript.\n42\t- Any string literals or glob patterns that reference the `.log` extension.\n43\t\n44\tThis is a straightforward find-and-replace scoped to this single file.\n45\t\n46\t## Acceptance Criteria\n47\t\n48\t- [ ] AC-1: `commit_transcript` looks for `.jsonl` files in `.harness-transcripts/`.\n49\t- [ ] AC-2: Committed transcripts are written to `.darkfactory/transcripts/` with `.jsonl` extension.\n50\t- [ ] AC-3: No references to `.log` transcripts remain in `commit_transcript.py`.\n51\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"34e46cdc-3fb0-4a48-851b-223c92f28d9a","uuid":"5568cb7b-7dba-4f66-95dd-0fc2b2c865d1","timestamp":"2026-04-09T07:50:53.734Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.darkfactory/prds/PRD-560.2-update-commit-transcript-extension.md","content":"---\nid: PRD-560.2\ntitle: Update commit_transcript.py for .jsonl extension\nkind: task\nstatus: ready\npriority: medium\neffort: xs\ncapability: simple\nparent: \"[[PRD-560-transcripts-should-be-jsonl-files]]\"\ndepends_on:\n  - \"[[PRD-560.1-rewrite-transcript-assembly-jsonl]]\"\nblocks: []\nimpacts:\n  - src/darkfactory/builtins/commit_transcript.py\nworkflow:\ntarget_version:\ncreated: 2026-04-09\nupdated: 2026-04-09\ntags: []\n---\n\n# Update commit_transcript.py for .jsonl extension\n\n## Summary\n\nUpdate `commit_transcript.py` to look for `.jsonl` transcript files instead of `.log` files when copying from the transient location to the committed location. Change both the source glob/path and the destination filename to use the `.jsonl` extension.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. Change the transient transcript source path from `.harness-transcripts/{prd_id}.log` to `.harness-transcripts/{prd_id}.jsonl`.\n2. Change the committed transcript destination path from `.darkfactory/transcripts/{prd_id}-{timestamp}.log` to `.darkfactory/transcripts/{prd_id}-{timestamp}.jsonl`.\n3. Ensure any glob patterns or file-existence checks in the commit logic reference `.jsonl`.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### File: `src/darkfactory/builtins/commit_transcript.py` (~lines 36-58)\n\nFind all references to `.log` in this file and replace with `.jsonl`. This includes:\n\n- The source path construction for finding the transient transcript.\n- The destination path construction for the committed transcript.\n- Any string literals or glob patterns that reference the `.log` extension.\n\nThis is a straightforward find-and-replace scoped to this single file.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `commit_transcript` looks for `.jsonl` files in `.harness-transcripts/`.\n- [ ] AC-2: Committed transcripts are written to `.darkfactory/transcripts/` with `.jsonl` extension.\n- [ ] AC-3: No references to `.log` transcripts remain in `commit_transcript.py`.\n","numLines":51,"startLine":1,"totalLines":51}}}
